name: float_f32_smallest_positive_normal
description: |
  This is the smallest positive normal binary32 value, 2^-126. It is adjacent
  to the largest subnormal despite using a different exponent/significand
  interpretation, making the pair useful for testing decoders, nextafter,
  ordering, and underflow thresholds.
format: hex
decode-as: f32
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "normal"
  - "underflow"
  - "boundary"
---
00 00 80 00   # 0x00800000: 2^-126
